File: A laboratory assistant works on a test sample of a suspected case of the coronavirus. JOHANNESBURG - The number of confirmed coronavirus cases in South Africa has risen to 1686. There has also been another death. The death of a 57-year-old man from the Western Cape takes the total death toll to 12. Health Minister Zweli Mkhize confirmed the latest figures on Monday. Gauteng has the highest number of infections standing at 713, while the Northern Cape has the least cases. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. Health Media Release 06.04.PDF.pdf (1) by eNCA.com on Scribd  The total number of COVID-19 tests conducted to date is 58 098.